POETRY

In
the
early
days
of
the
year
1911,
a
young
man
who
was
very

badly
dressed
went
running
up
the
rue
Houdon.
His
extremely
mo

bile
countenance
seemed
to
be
filled
with
joy
and
anxiety
by
turns.

His
eyes
devoured
all
that
they
saw
and
when
his
eyelids
snapped
shut

quickly
like
jaws,
they
gulped
in
the
universe,
which
renewed
itself

incessantly

the
mere
operation

who
ran.

imagined
to

details

about
